page.title: 02HIGH STREET KEMPSTON
page.content: { High Street is one of the {oldest {streets}in Kempston. Buildings have stood on this street since medieval times.It is a{residential}and {commercial}street.At the top the street stands the war memorial and many shops.Older houses are found at the end of the street.The south_east side of the street has no houses because the{Brook floods}occasionally. Halfway down High street,the Brook is channelled under the road and down Water Lane to the{River Ouse.}One large house 'The Barns' has been altered and extended as a hostel for teenage girls. There is also an{Old {People's Home}called Brookside. The street has three public houses <notable is the{King William IV,}a beamed building> and a modern methodist church.
